1. What is Betalingsservice?
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
.br
Betalingsservice is a payment service which enables the customer to pay
bills in DKK to creditors registered in the system. Once the customer has
given a BS mandate to his or her creditor, the creditor is authorised
to collect payments from from the customer's account.
.br
Betalingsservice is a system designed for recurring payments, but the
creditor may also execute one-off payments and pay e.g. excess amounts
paid on account into the customer's account.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
2. Definitions
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
2.1 Refusal
:SKRSLUT.
.br
:SWISS8.
If payment is refused, the system will not execute the payment
transaction. The customer may refuse a future payment in accordance
with the provisions set out in clause 8.1.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.2 Banking day
:SKRSLUT.
.br
:SWISS8.
Banking days are all days except Saturdays, Sundays, Danish public
holidays, the Friday after Ascension Day, 5 June, 24 December and 31
December.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.3 Betalingsservice mandate (BS mandate)
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A BS mandate is an agreement between the customer and a creditor
authorising the creditor to collect payments from the customer using
Betalingsservice. The customer may give a BS mandate directly to the
creditor or through &BANKNAVN. acting on behalf of the creditor.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.4 Payment date
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The payment date is the day on which the amount is debited to the
customer's account. Payments are executed on banking days only.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.5 Betalingsservice prenotification
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The Betalingsservice prenotification lists the following month's
Betalingsservice payments from the customer's account. The customer
will receive his or her prenotification electronically or by ordinary
mail just before the change of month.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.6 Electronic payment information
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The customer may choose to receive electronic payment information in
his or her online banking system or electronic mailbox.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.7 Electronic mailbox
:SKRSLUT.
.br
An electronic mailbox is a system allowing the customer to receive
electronic payment information.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.8 &NETS.
:SKRSLUT.
.br
&NETS. Denmark A/S, CVR No. &PBSCVR. is the company that operates
Betalingsservice. As payment service provider, &NETS. is
subject to supervision by the Danish
Financial Supervisory Authority.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.9 Return
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Return of a payment means that the amount is returned from the creditor's
account to the customer's account. The customer or &BANKNAVN. may request a
transfer of a payment already executed if the conditions are met, see
clause 8.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.10 Betalingsservice debtor agreement (BS debtor agreement)
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A debtor agreement is an agreement between the customer and
&BANKNAVN. authorising the customer to pay bills through Betalingsservice.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
3. Registration for Betalingsservice
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
3.1 The BS debtor agreement
:SKRSLUT.
.br
It is a condition for using Betalingsservice that the customer has
concluded a BS debtor agreement with &BANKNAVN.. If the customer wishes to
use Betalingsservice, the customer must contact &BANKNAVN..
.br
&BANKNAVN. is not obliged to conclude a BS debtor agreement with the
customer but will make an individual assessment as to whether the customer
may use Betalingsservice.
.br
Once the customer has a BS debtor agreement, the customer may give BS
mandates.
.br
If the customer has no BS debtor agreement, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to
return payments already effected and cancel BS mandates in accordance with
the provisions set out in clause 8.3.
.sp 3mm
:FED.
3.2 Rules
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The BS debtor agreement obliges the customer to comply with the General
conditions for Betalingsservice debtors.
