6. Special rules on electronic payment information
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
6.1 Agreement on electronic payment information
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The customer must make an agreement with &BANKNAVN. if the customer wants
to receive electronic payment information only.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the customer later decides that he og she would like to receive
printed prenotifications, thecustomer must amend the agreement with
&BANKNAVN. accordingly.
Termination of the customer's online banking agreement will automatically
terminate the agreement on electronic payment information. Instead, the
customer will receive printed Betalingsservice prenotifications, provided
that the BS debtor agreement has not been terminated.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
6.2 The customer's obligations in connection with electronic payment
information
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the customer have opted for electronic information only, the customer is
responsible for checking that he or she has actually received such
information. The customer must contact &BANKNAVN. immediately if the
customer has not received the electronic payment information the customer
expected at the beginning of the month or if the customer has found errors
in his or her equipment preventing the customer from receiving  the payment
information electronically. &BANKNAVN. will resend payment information
electronically or in print.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the customer fails to contact &BANKNAVN. immediately, the customer may
forfeit the option of refusing a payment, see clause 8.1. The customer is
responsible for ensuring that his or her own equipment is set up to
receive electronic payment information. The customer is also liable if
failure to access the information is due to his or her telecommunications
operator or Internet service provider.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
