7. Payment execution
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
7.1 Consent to payment execution
:SKRSLUT.
.br
When the customer gives a BS mandate to a creditor, the customer consents
to the execution of payments under the agreement. The customer may revoke
his or her consent by cancelling the BS mandate (see clause 10.1) or
by enforcing his or her right to refuse or request a refund of a payment in
accordance with the provisions set out in clause 8.1.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If no valid BS mandate exists, the customer may dispute payments, see
clause 9.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.2 Funds in the customer's account
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The customer's account must hold sufficient funds at the payment date. If
the funds in the customer's account are insufficient to meet all payments
that fall due on a payment date, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to return these
payments in accordance with the provisions set out in clause
.if &U'&WEBPRIERH eq E
.th  9.
.el 8.3.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.3 Payment execution date
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A payment is debited to the customer's account on the payment date
specified by the creditor.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.4 Specification of payment date
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The creditor must specify the payment date in accordance with the
customer's agreement. The customer and his or her creditor must agree on
changes to payment dates.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.5 Payment and receipt
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Collection of payments through Betalingsservice will discharge the customer
from his or her payment obligation to his or her creditor.
An account statement specifying the payment is considered evidence of
execution. This does not apply, however, if the payment is subsequently
refunded or returned by &BANKNAVN..
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the customer wants a separate receipt for a payment executed during the
past 15 months, the customer must contact &BANKNAVN..
&BANKNAVN. will inform the customer of the charge for this service on
request.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
7.6 Maximum execution time
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The maximum total execution time is one banking day.
