9. Disputing payments
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
9.1 Unauthorised and incorrectly executed payments
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Payments are unauthorised if no valid BS mandate exists.
Payments are incorrectly executed if they are not registered and booked
correctly or if they are affected by technical failure or similar failure
caused by &NETS. or &BANKNAVN., for example a discrepancy
between the notified amount and the booked amount.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS8.
:FED.
9.2 The customer's options
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The customer may submit an objection to &BANKNAVN. stating that
.br
.of 5mm
*¤the customer has not given a BS mandate to the creditor for the payment
in question; or
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤the payment in question is incorrect.
.of
.sp 3mm
If the customer believes that a executed payment is unauthorised or
incorrectly executed, the customer must contact &BANKNAVN. as soon as
possible after detecting the failure and no later than 13 months after the
payment date.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the payment is unauthorised or incorrectly executed, the payment will be
returned through &BANKNAVN.. The customer's position will be the same as
before execution of the payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS8.
:FED.
9.3 Deadlines
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the deadline for submitting the customer's objection is a nonbanking
day, the actual deadline is the following banking day.
